	<a href="https://sleepy-fortress-4999.herokuapp.com/#/"><h4>Town Share</h4></a>
	<p>
		As a collective project between friends, Town Share set out to bring neighbors together by gamifying community service. Think of it as craigslist meets yelp in game form. Neighbors do tasks for one another to receiver points which they can then in turn use for tasks to be done for oneself.
		Participants not only receive points, but they also gain experience and ratings which can be monitored on the leader board! As team lead I had to make sure work was progressing forward in a way that enabled my teammates to work independently without stepping on each other's toes.
		My favorite part of managing a team is igniting each team members individual passion and letting them express themselves. On this project we used Angular on the front end and Node/Express on the backend. Other features include Facebook OAuth, password reset with nodemailer, and user profiles.
	</p>
